<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-07T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-07T01:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.61331/187: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sokobin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-07T14:00:00+08:00">December
                                    7, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 7—9:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>221. Universal Leaf Tobacco Company will sign agreement tomorrow morning
                            with the Japanese military mission covering rights of purchase of
                            1,600,000 pounds of leaf tobacco at five places on the railway,
                            including Tsingtao, under conditions along the lines of those outlined
                            in my telegram 212, November 13, 11 a.m., but with more liberal
                            construction and concessions and with clause which will enable company
                            to purchase beyond the instant allotment if the size of the crop
                            permits.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping, Shanghai. Tokyo informed by telegram.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sokobin</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>